author: Steve Schering
title: Fire department 'quickly' extinguishes south Oak Park garage fire - Oak Leaves
text:
Firefighters from the Oak Park Fire Department were called to a small garage fire in south Oak Park Oct. 6 and quickly extinguished the flames.
Fire Department officials say they were dispatched to a home in the 1100 block of South Taylor Avenue shortly after 4:20 p.m., where they found a fire in the garage just behind the home.
"It was a detached garage fire," said firefighter/EMT Zach Byington. "We were able to put it out fairly quickly. It's a total loss. It was not what you'd call a sturdy garage."
Byington said there were no injuries to report.
As of Oct. 7, the structure was still standing and showed minimal affects of the fire on its exterior.
